Sentencas: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3 (LCC)-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 (GDC) composites have been investigated as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) on La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte, where there is no interlayer between anode and electrolyte.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LCC oxide is chemically compatible with GDC and LSGM electrolyte at temperatures up to 1200 degrees C.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the LCC-GDC composites decreases with increasing GDC content.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The best electrical conductivities of 18.64 S cm(-1) in air and 1.86 S cm(-1) in H-2 at 850 degrees C are achieved for an 80 wt% LCC-20 wt%
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells
La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficients of the LCC-GDC composites increase with increasing GDC content, and are very close to that of the LSGM electrolyte.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A cell with a 0.3 mm thick LSGM electrolyte and LCC-GDC20 symmetrical electrodes displays the highest electrochemical performance.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density is 573 mW cm(-2) in dry H-2 and 333 mW cm-2 in humidified commercial city gas containing H2S at 900 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: These results suggest that the LCC-GDC20 composite can potentially serve as an electrode for symmetrical SOFCs operated on H-2 and commercial city gas containing H2S. (c) 2010 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.
Titulo: La0.7Ca0.3CrO3-Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 composites as symmetrical electrodes for solid-oxide fuel cells
